-- Slovakia Considers to Lease Bratislava Airport, Sme Reports
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2012-04-17T06:50:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/slovakia-considers-to-lease-bratislava-airport-sme-reports.html
The Slovak government is
considering leasing Bratislava airport, the country’s busiest,
to a strategic investor,  Sme  reported, citing Deputy Finance
Minister Peter Pellegrini.  The government estimates that the airport, located near the
country’s capital, needs about 350 million euros ($458 million)
in investment within the next ten years to remain competitive,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  